HEADWORD: Outreign
<hw>Out*reign"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To go beyond in
reigning; to reign through the whole of, or longer than.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

